Object literals have gotten a new shorthand notation `{name: name, title: title}` can be condensed to `{name, title}`

    const foo = "foo";
    const bar = function () {
      return "bar";
    };

    const a = {foo, bar};

    console.log(a); // Object {foo: "foo", bar: function}

